org.hibernate.ogm.util.impl

Class AssociationPersister

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.util.impl.AssociationPersister

  • public class AssociationPersister
extends Object
    Implements the logic for updating associations. Configured in a fluent manner, followed by a call to flushToDatastore() which invokes the given GridDialect to apply the changes to the datastore.

    Unlike ORM style persisters, this class is tied to a specific association instance with specific ids. In other words, instances cannot be shared by SessionFactory level objects like EntityPersister.

    Author:
    Emmanuel Bernard, Gunnar Morling

      • hostingEntityRequiresReadAfterUpdate

        public boolean hostingEntityRequiresReadAfterUpdate()
        Whether the association in question is stored within an entity structure ("embedded") and this entity has properties whose value is generated in the datastore (such as a version attribute) or not.
        Returns:
        true in case the represented association is stored within an entity which has server-generated properties, and thus must be re-read after an update to the association, false otherwise.
